The paper deals with the construction and analysis of quasi-Gray codes, which are combinatorial objects used in data structures and coding theory. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) the most likely category. The paper also uses algebraic tools and principles of catalytic computation, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper involves combinatorial designs and constructions, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
